revisions.rev:
'''Homeless dumping''' is the practice of hospital employees or emergency workers releasing [[homeless]] patients on the streets instead of placing them into the custody of a relative or [[homeless shelter|shelter]] or retaining them in a hospital where they may require expensive medical care. <ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Dumped On Skid Row |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2007/05/17/60minutes/main2823079.shtml |work= |publisher=[[60 Minutes]] |date= |accessdate=2007-05-21 }}</ref> <ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=L.A. charges hospital in dumping of homeless |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/15752013 |work= |publisher=[[MSNBC]] |date=[[November 16]], [[2006]] |accessdate=2007-05-21 }}</ref>
{{Cleanup-remainder|date=June 2007}}
==Usage== *[[Associated Press]]; [[February 9]], [[2007]]; [[Los Angeles]]. A hospital van dropped off a homeless paraplegic man on Skid Row and left him crawling in the street with nothing more than a soiled gown and a broken colostomy bag, police said.... Police said the incident was a case of ''"homeless dumping"'' and were questioning officials from the hospital.<ref>[http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/17062674/ Police probe alleged L.A. homeless dumping: Hospital van reportedly spotted dropping off paraplegic man on [[Skid Row]]], [[MSNBC]] via [[Associated Press]], [[February 9]], [[2007]]</ref>
*[[Associated Press]], [[October 25]], [[2006]]; [[Los Angeles]]. "L.A. Police Allege ''Homeless Dumping''." Authorities have launched a criminal investigation into suspected dumping of homeless people on Skid Row after police witnessed ambulances leaving five people on a street there during the weekend.
